\pard\f0\fs28 Var.{\i   gayanum} Godron, from S.W. France and Spain, may merit subspecific rank. It has the leaflets of the basal leaves broadly elliptical or sub-orbicular; heads solitary; peduncles 100-150 mm, sparsely hairy; pedicels 2 mm, as long as the calyx-tube and exceeding the bracts, deflexed in fruit; and the calyx-tube glabrescent, with oblique mouth.
